```console
$ mkdir -p /var/appjail-volumes/shiori
$ appjail oci run -Pd \
    -o overwrite=force \
    -o virtualnet=":<random> default" \
    -o nat \
    -o fstab="/var/appjail-volumes/shiori/data /var/db/shiori" \
    -o expose=8080 \
    ghcr.io/appjail-makejails/shiori shiori
```

Once Shiori is up and running, you can access its web interface at `http://shiori:8080` or `http://your-host-ip:8080` (from external hosts).

Another way to access your bookmarks is through the CLI:

```console
$ appjail oci exec shiori shiori print
WARN[2026-07-22T01:14:30-04:00] SHIORI_HTTP_SECRET_KEY is not set, using random value. This means that all sessions will be invalidated on server restart.
1. https://example.org
   > https://example.org

```
